<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Polo de Bernabé</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-02"><hi rend="italic">April 2,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Polo</hi>: I have to thank you for your
                            prompt reply to my note of the 31st ultimo, informing me that to your
                            belief the general designation “western provinces” is applied to and
                            includes the provinces of Havana, Matanzas, Santa Clara, and Pinar del
                            Rio.</p>
                        <p>Believe me, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>